  <!-- LOW-3: git config in read-only allowlist -->
  <div class="finding" data-severity="low">
    <div class="finding-header">
      <span class="arrow">&#9654;</span>
      <span class="severity low">Low</span>
      <span class="title"><code>git config</code> Allowed in Read-Only Mode</span>
      <span class="file-badge">bash_validation.rs:183</span>
    </div>
    <div class="finding-body">
      <h4>Description</h4>
      <p><code>git config</code> is listed in the read-only safe subcommands, but <code>git config --global user.name "..."</code> can write to <code>~/.gitconfig</code>, modifying state outside the workspace.</p>

      <h4>Affected Code</h4>
<pre class="code"><span class="cmt">// bash_validation.rs:163</span>
<span class="kw">const</span> GIT_READ_ONLY_SUBCOMMANDS: &amp;[&amp;<span class="type">str</span>] = &amp;[
    <span class="str">"status"</span>, <span class="str">"log"</span>, <span class="str">"diff"</span>, <span class="str">"show"</span>, <span class="str">"branch"</span>, <span class="str">"tag"</span>,
    <span class="str">"stash"</span>, <span class="str">"remote"</span>, <span class="str">"fetch"</span>, <span class="str">"ls-files"</span>, <span class="str">"ls-tree"</span>,
    <span class="str">"cat-file"</span>, <span class="str">"rev-parse"</span>, <span class="str">"describe"</span>, <span class="str">"shortlog"</span>,
    <span class="str">"blame"</span>, <span class="str">"bisect"</span>, <span class="str">"reflog"</span>, <span class="str">"config"</span>, <span class="cmt">// &lt;-- can write</span>
];</pre>

      <div class="recommendation">
        <strong>Recommendation:</strong> Remove <code>config</code> from the read-only allowlist, or add a sub-check that only allows <code>git config --get</code> and <code>git config --list</code> in read-only mode.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

